    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If there's a delay or a dispute during the closing process, the escrow agent plays a crucial role in resolving the issue. The escrow agent will review the terms of the agreement and the relevant documents to determine if the conditions for releasing the funds have been met. If there are missing documents or discrepancies, the escrow agent will typically communicate with both parties to clarify the situation and identify the missing information or paperwork.\n\nIn the case of a dispute, the escrow agent may request additional documentation or clarification from both the buyer and the seller. If the issue cannot be resolved through communication and negotiation, the escrow agent may involve a mediator or a legal professional to help facilitate a resolution.\n\nIt's important to note that the escrow agent's primary responsibility is to ensure that the transaction is completed fairly and in accordance with the terms of the agreement. They act as a neutral party to protect the interests of both the buyer and the seller. If the dispute cannot be resolved and the conditions for releasing the funds are not met, the escrow agent will hold onto the funds until the issue is resolved.\n\nIn some cases, if the dispute cannot be resolved, the escrow agent may release the funds to the seller, but the buyer may have the right to pursue legal action to recover their funds. It's",
